args: (I've already sent so many letters,\nbut haven't gotten a single reply.)
No, of course not!\nShe's fine. I know it.
I wrote all about how I helped out with\nDragonyule this year, so I'm sure she'll\nwant to write me back this time!
Eek! You surprised me. What is it?
Um, we brought you a Dragonyule\npresent!
No buts! Not after you went so far out of\nyour way to help prepare for the party.
Think of it as our little way of saying\nthanks. Here you go!
Ta-daaa! They're cookies! Lowen's big\nsister taught us how to make them.
Louise is a whiz in the kitchen. I only hope\nwe were able to do her recipe justice.
They smell amazing! Thanks so much!
Looks like they beat us here.
Maribelle! You can't just call people\n＂rough 'n tumble＂!
We came to give Lily a gift.
You too? We just gave her some cookies.
Y'know, to show her how we appreciate\nher hard work as Saint Starfall!
Well, that makes four of us, then.\nWould you accept this gift from us, Lily?
We got you this hairpin. It's designed\nto look like a snowflake. Pretty, isn't it?
Durant's the one who picked it out,\nbelieve it or not.
Don't slander me with lies, dammit!\nSheesh...
Anyway, I said we'd give you a gift, so... \nHere. Knock yourself out.
Thank you! I'll treasure it forever!
Hee hee. We must all be thinking\nthe same thing.
We're all so grateful to you,\nSaint Starfall Lily.
You gave us the gift of happiness,\nand for that, we thank you.
All this time, I've only ever frozen things...\nbut now, my heart is full and warm!
I could never have had such a happy\nholiday if I didn't have all of you.
(I'm tickled with these gifts,\nbut you know what matters most?)
Even though I was Saint Starfall, you\nall showed me the spirit of the season.
Thank you so much for giving me the\ngift of a happy Dragonyule, everybody!
